iler with `-L` instead of using the `--extern lib_name=path-to-rlib` compiler argument form. This is a shame because the latter form is what cargo actually uses in practice!\r\n\r\nWe ought to add another comment form to use the latter. Something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\n// aux-build:lib_name=file.rs\r\n```\r\n\r\nor perhaps a different header name.\r\n\r\n(We could also retrofit the existing `aux-build` to use `--extern`, but it seems useful to be able to test in both modes, actually, so I'd prefer to add something new.)\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/53737/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/53737/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}